    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-15T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="1034"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1034">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">300.1115/8–1545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-15T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 15, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1260. Dept. informed by Navy Dept that Naval forces operating in southern China
                    report recovery of American CIs<note n="13" xml:id="d1034fn13">Civilian
                        Internees.</note> and/or POWs<note n="14" xml:id="d1034fn14">Prisoners of
                        War.</note> recently abandoned by Jap occupation forces. Obtain from Am mil
                    auth names of Am CIs now or later liberated and telegraph names to Dept.</p>
                <p>In view current developments alert Consuls to necessity of obtaining and
                    transmitting info about liberated Am nationals. Invite Consuls’ attention to
                    Foreign Service Serial No. 353, April 17, 1945,<note n="15" xml:id="d1034fn15"
                        >Circular Instruction to American Diplomtic and Consular Officers,
                        “Emergency Financial Assistance Loans to Destitute American Nationals in
                        Foreign Countries for Subsistence and Repatriation”.</note> providing for
                    emergency financial assistance loans to destitute Am nationals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
